# Copy this file to ``.env`` (``make setup`` does it for you on first run).
# .env is gitignored — never commit it.
#
# All values below are OPTIONAL. The framework only reads them when the
# corresponding mode is requested:
#   - MODE=fixtures / scenario / fault  → no .env needed at all
#   - MODE=production / hybrid          → reads DATABRICKS_PROFILE (and
#                                         MONGO_URI if the pipeline pulls
#                                         from Mongo).
#   - MODE=production-schema            → same as production.

# Profile name in ~/.databrickscfg. Created via:
#   databricks auth login --host https://<workspace>.cloud.databricks.com \
#                         --profile dbc-fe98d761-8813
# The default profile name matches the workspace already used by metatron/local.py.
DATABRICKS_PROFILE=dbc-fe98d761-8813

# Catalog + schema that production-mode runs read from. Defaults match
# scripts/common/config_loader.py and pipelines/metatron.yaml.
# Set DATABRICKS_CATALOG=metatron to point production-mode runs at prod.
# DATABRICKS_CATALOG=metatron_dev
# DATABRICKS_SCHEMA=master

# MongoDB connection string. Only needed if the pipeline you're verifying
# reads from a Mongo collection (see ``MongoSource`` in pipeline.py).
# Ask the team for a read-only connection string.
# MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://user:pass@host/
